<br>
Pre-prohibition of alcohol = occassional deaths related to alcohol useage.<br>
<br>
Prohibition = Occassional deaths related to alcohol useage <b>PLUS</b> deaths related to the criminal enterprise of alcohol production, distribution, competition, and lack of government quality control.<br>
<br>
Post-prohibition = occassional deaths related to alcohol useage again.<br>
<br>
1. Drugs kill people, but not nearly as many people as the <b>War on Drugs</b> kills.<br>
<br>
2. Source Check: Please provide your source for the rape/murder statistic. <br>
<br>
3. We have no greater freedom then the freedom to live our lives as we see fit. You cannot take away freedoms from the innocent because the guilty will not play by societies rules.<br>
<br>
If someone commits rape or murder - you punish them for it. <br>
Drugs are not the cause, or there would be no sober rapes. <br>
If drugs aren't the cause, what does it matter that they used them before the crime?<br>
I am sure many of them watched televison prior to the rape also, does this mean televison causes rape and murder?<br>
<br>
Yes, some people steal to support drugs. Some people also steal to feed their families. Who the hell cares why they steal?<br>
This is as stupid as "Hate Crime" legizlation. What does it matter what motivates someone to hurt someone else - hurting people is already illegal! Punish them for it - and forget about why they did it.<br>
<br>
It is clear from your earlier posts that you have no understanding of freedom whatsoever - as you believe it acceptable for you to make all of your friends choices for them.<br>
<br>
Simply put - people should be 100% free to do whatever they want - as long as it doesn't interfere with anyone else's right to do the same.<br>
<br>
If they infringe on someone elses rights by raping, murdering, stealing, etc. - you punish them for it. <br>
If they don't you butt the hell out of there life and mind your own damned business!<br>
<br>
You sure as shit don't go to their home and destroy their property, like you do with your friend's cigarettes.<br>
<br>
